<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-24T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="1119" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1119">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">831.6363/5–246</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-24T19:00:00-04:00">May 24, 1946—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>235. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 291, May 20.<note n="68" xml:id="d1119fn68">Not printed.</note> After <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> has been informed that Pantepec has filed protest and
                            providing <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> is so requested, you are
                            authorized to communicate at an opportune time with the appropriate
                            officials of the Govt orally and informally on subject of excess profits
                            tax decree of Dec 31. Your remarks might appropriately allude to
                            statements made at time decree was issued and refer to Pantepec protest
                            as an example of hardships brought about by decree. Dept does not feel
                            that situation requires a position stronger than that indicated
                            above.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>